==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ween
<hw>Ween</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>wenen</ets>,
AS. <ets>w<?/nan</ets>, fr. <ets>w<?/n</ets> hope, expectation, opinion;
akin to D. <ets>waan</ets>, OFries. <ets>w<?/n</ets>, OS. & OHG.
<ets>w⟦amac⟧n</ets>, G. <ets>wahn</ets> delusion, Icel.
<ets>v⟦amac⟧n</ets> hope, expectation, Goth. <ets>w<?/ns</ets>, and D.
<ets>wanen</ets> to fancy, G. <ets>w⟦aum⟧hnen</ets>, Icel.
<ets>v⟦amac⟧na</ets> to hope, Goth. <ets>w<?/njan</ets>, and perhaps to
E. <ets>winsome</ets>, <ets>wish</ets>.]</ety> <def>To think; to
imagine; to fancy.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Poetic]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.
Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have lost more than thou <qex>wenest</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For well I <qex>ween</qex>,⟦br⟧
Never before in the bowers of light⟦br⟧
Had the form of an earthly fay been seen.</q> <rj><qau>J. R.
Drake.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though never a dream the roses sent⟦br⟧
Of science or love's compliment,⟦br⟧
I <qex>ween</qex> they smelt as sweet.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weep</ent>⟦br⟧
